In this memorandum, President Barack Obama delegates authority to the Secretary of State to direct the drawdown of up to $25 million in defense articles and services from the Department of Defense. This is to provide immediate military assistance to the Government of Iraq, including the Kurdistan Regional Government, in their efforts to combat the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant. The Secretary of State is also authorized to make the necessary determinations required under the Foreign Assistance Act of 1961 to carry out this drawdown. The memorandum concludes by instructing the Secretary of State to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.